    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-08-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-08-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="307"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d307">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-08-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 25, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Rockhill asks if this Government agrees to British proposal concerning
                    surplus indemnity, referred to in his telegram of the 10th instant.</p>
                <p>The Chinese plenipotentiaries are still waiting authorization of Chinese
                    Government to sign protocol.</p>
                <pb facs="0387" n="381" xml:id="pg_381"/>
                <p>Mr. Rockhill will remain at Peking until the matter is settled.</p>
                <p>Replying to Mr. Hay’s telegram<note n="1" xml:id="d307fn1">Not printed.</note> to
                    Mr. Conger, composition of Commission for the revision of the tariff and place
                    of meeting not yet settled. * * *)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
